---
// Privacy policy (EN mirror of /datenschutz.html — same slug so the language
// switcher pairs the pages). Describes factually what this static site does.
// [TODO] fields must be filled before publishing.
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteNav from '../components/SiteNav.astro';
import Attribution from '../components/Attribution.astro';
---
<Layout title={"Privacy Policy | VerseBase"} description={"Privacy policy of VerseBase: a static website without cookies or tracking — what data is processed when visiting, when external images load, and when YouTube videos are clicked."} themeColor="#05070d" translated={true}>
<style is:inline>
:root{--bg:#05070d;--bg-2:#0a0e18;--surface:#0f1524;--surface-2:#141c30;--accent:#2dd4ff;--accent-2:#6ea8ff;--text:#e8eefc;--muted:#8a99b8;--line:rgba(110,168,255,.16);--line-soft:rgba(232,238,252,.10);--ink:#05070d;--maxw:840px;}
.lg-wrap{max-width:var(--maxw);margin:0 auto;padding:3.2rem 1.25rem 4rem}
.lg-wrap h1{font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:900;font-size:clamp(2rem,6vw,3rem);color:#fff;margin:0 0 1.6rem}
.lg-wrap h2{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;font-size:.95rem;color:var(--accent);margin:2.2rem 0 .6rem;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);padding-bottom:.4rem}
.lg-wrap p, .lg-wrap li{color:var(--text);line-height:1.7;font-size:.98rem}
.lg-wrap ul{padding-left:1.2rem}
.lg-wrap .muted{color:var(--muted)}
.lg-fill{display:inline-block;background:color-mix(in srgb,#ff5b5b 14%,transparent);border:1px dashed #ff5b5b;border-radius:4px;padding:0 .45rem;color:#ffb4b4;font-weight:700}
</style>
<SiteNav crumbs={[{ label: 'Archive', href: '/archiv.html' }, { label: 'Privacy' }]} hasEn={true} />
<main id="main">
  <div class="lg-wrap">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <h2>Controller</h2>
    <p>
      Krisztofer Milánkovits, Schlossstraße 6, 85411 Hohenkammer, Germany —
      e-mail: <a href="mailto:krysx141@gmail.com">krysx141@gmail.com</a>
    </p>

    <h2>Principle</h2>
    <p>
      This website is a purely static, non-commercial fan project. It uses <strong>no cookies</strong>,
      <strong>no analytics or tracking services</strong>, no advertising and no comment functions.
      Simply viewing the site transmits no personal data from you to us. The only exceptions are the
      <a href="#feedback">feedback form</a> and the optional <a href="#accounts">user account</a> —
      both voluntary; the data processed there is described separately below.
    </p>

    <h2>Server log files (hosting)</h2>
    <p>
      When you visit this website, the hosting provider
      Hetzner Online GmbH (Industriestr. 25, 91710 Gunzenhausen, Germany) technically
      processes connection data (IP address, timestamp, requested resource, user agent) in server
      logs. Legal basis: Art. 6 (1) (f) GDPR (legitimate interest in secure operation).
    </p>

    <h2>Local browser storage (localStorage)</h2>
    <p>
      Some tools on this site (e.g. the crafting planner, “owned” marks, view settings) store their
      state exclusively <strong>locally in your browser</strong> (localStorage). This data never
      leaves your device and can be deleted at any time via your browser settings.
    </p>

    <h2>Externally embedded images</h2>
    <p>
      Some imagery is loaded from external sources. When these images are fetched, your IP address
      is technically transmitted to the respective provider:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>fleetyards.net</strong> — ship and vehicle imagery</li>
      <li><strong>starcitizen.tools / cstone.space</strong> — individual media assets</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Ambient background videos</h2>
    <p>
      Some pages show short, muted video loops (trailer excerpts) as backgrounds. These files
      are served <strong>locally by this website</strong> — no third-party server is contacted.
      With reduced motion enabled (prefers-reduced-motion), an active data-saver mode, or on
      small screens, only the still image is loaded instead.
    </p>

    <h2>YouTube videos (click to load)</h2>
    <p>
      Videos are embedded as preview stills and load <strong>only after you click</strong>, via
      youtube-nocookie.com (Google Ireland Ltd.). Before the click, no connection to Google is made;
      after the click, <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener">Google’s privacy policy</a> applies.
    </p>

    <h2 id="feedback">Feedback form (Web3Forms)</h2>
    <p>
      On the <a href="/feedback.html">Feedback</a> page you can voluntarily send us a message.
      Because this website is static and has no server backend of its own, delivery is handled by the
      service <strong>Web3Forms</strong>. When you submit, the following data is transmitted to
      Web3Forms and delivered from there to us by e-mail:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>message text</strong> (required)</li>
      <li><strong>rating</strong> (1–5 stars, optional)</li>
      <li><strong>e-mail address</strong> (optional — only if you want a reply; it is set as the
        reply-to address)</li>
      <li>technically, your IP address and the time of submission</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The legal basis is your consent given by actively submitting the form (Art. 6 (1) (a) GDPR).
      Providing your e-mail address is voluntary; without it we cannot reply to your feedback. We use
      the data solely to process and answer your feedback and do not pass it on for other purposes.
    </p>
    <p class="muted">
      The form service is provided by Web3Forms. Transmission may involve processing on servers
      outside the EU. For details on how the service processes data, see its privacy policy:
      <a href="https://web3forms.com/privacy" rel="noopener">web3forms.com/privacy</a>. The form sets
      no cookies and loads no external scripts; a connection to Web3Forms is only established upon
      submission.
    </p>

    <h2 id="accounts">User account (Supabase)</h2>
    <p>
      You can voluntarily create a user account to save favorites (e.g. bookmarked ships) and manage
      a profile. The account feature is provided via <strong>Supabase</strong>; the data is stored in
      an EU data center (AWS Frankfurt, region eu-central-1). The following data is processed:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>e-mail address</strong> and <strong>password</strong> (the password is stored
        exclusively as a cryptographic hash, never in plain text)</li>
      <li><strong>profile data</strong> you enter yourself (display name, handle — both optional)</li>
      <li><strong>favorites</strong> you actively save</li>
      <li>technically, session and security data of the provider (e.g. sign-in timestamps,
        IP address in security logs)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The legal basis is Art. 6 (1) (b) GDPR (providing the account feature at your request).
      Sign-in works without cookies: the session token is stored exclusively locally in your browser
      (localStorage). You can permanently delete your account yourself at any time in the
      <a href="/account.html">account dashboard</a> — this irreversibly removes all associated
      data (profile, favorites, credentials).
    </p>
    <p class="muted">
      Processor: Supabase, Inc.; data residency in the EU (AWS eu-central-1, Frankfurt). For details
      on how the service processes data, see
      <a href="https://supabase.com/privacy" rel="noopener">supabase.com/privacy</a>.
      A connection to Supabase is only established when you use account features
      (registration, sign-in, favorites) — not when merely browsing the site.
    </p>

    <h2>Fonts</h2>
    <p>All web fonts are served locally by this website. No connection to Google Fonts is made.</p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      You have the rights under Art. 15–21 GDPR (access, rectification, erasure, restriction, data
      portability, objection) and the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority
      (Art. 77 GDPR). Without a user account, this website does not collect or store personal data
      about you; with an account, you can view, change and fully delete your data yourself in the
      dashboard at any time — if in doubt, reach out by e-mail.
    </p>
  </div>
</main>
<Attribution sources={[]} />
</Layout>
